<subSubSection id="3B5DD3496C3B9F72C285CEBE1379FE69" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="notes">
<paragraph id="840E6D434C542EC16B38FE69CD6D9DD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E6DB36F2665E40DAEDC670D1AD569124" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="2F77BD0D65DCAB338F034D394D53AE67" authorityName="Cobos-Villagran, R. Valenz., Hdz. - Rdz., Calvillo-Medina &amp; Raymundo" authorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hysteriaceae" genus="Rhytidhysteron" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rhytidhysteron mesophilum" order="Patellariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mesophilum">
<emphasis id="B1FABC1C88532245DD42C8173D8A5A25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Rhytidhysteron mesophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by a dark green, dull green, greyish green, deep green to yellowish green hysterothecium, forming small ascomata within disc in old specimens. This fungus could be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="66D2268D461DFC8210A3E16DDFF41893" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. esperanzae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="esperanzae">
<emphasis id="4B5F20C3E3A8F4E7E5F681E34EE8372E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. esperanzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because both are found in tropical cloud forest (mesophilic forests) and have similar ascospores. However, 
<taxonomicName id="566DBFFB6D87F95FCA9CD59C18D6C1C1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. mesophilum" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mesophilum">
<emphasis id="CCF228FA07FD2B0C7BF69666B7F9D4C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. mesophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by a reddish orange to orange red epithecium, while in 
<taxonomicName id="7FBDAA9277285F2CE14AA73454585313" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. esperanzae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="esperanzae">
<emphasis id="B91002AF24DD48C59FAD87B4BFB6ECC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. esperanzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the epithecium is dark green to black. 
<taxonomicName id="0BD7457C80CB1F60FDF77FCF4F984FC7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. mesophilum" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mesophilum">
<emphasis id="1F34912EF4065DF6A647D2F5A36B7B19" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. mesophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also resembles 
<taxonomicName id="439B13B418327D39DFA857346F4A1C09" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. columbiense" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="columbiense">
<emphasis id="20E340C0616A27C5E3421C27844D4454" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. columbiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a yellowish green (30B-C8) pruina in the margin, but the ascospores are larger (38-52 
<normalizedToken id="772912BE0949AAF1A9FB7951C2BED9F1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
13-18 
<normalizedToken id="23B56C7891950756E914733B151B59BE" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and the epithecium is brown to dark brown in the second species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33905354B824D30ADEF562E12A150D39" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
A dichotomous key is presented with the species of 
<taxonomicName id="36D9673B9B623B04F2EC6DCF79C22F81" authorityName="Spegazzini" authorityYear="1881" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hysteriaceae" genus="Rhytidhysteron" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rhytidhysteron" order="Patellariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="64DD3AE54D4FEC6D18E53E5B7B97D4C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Rhytidhysteron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accepted by 
<bibRefCitation id="9F8B261AD475DFC59A19C0121A9B0351" author="Index Fungorum" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" publicationUrl="http://www.indexfungorum.org/names/Names.asp" refId="B22" refString="Index Fungorum, 2021. Index Fungorum. http://www.indexfungorum.org/names/Names.asp" title="Index Fungorum." url="http://www.indexfungorum.org/names/Names.asp" year="2021">Index Fungorum (2021)</bibRefCitation>
, including the three new species proposed in this work. The key includes the recently described 
<taxonomicName id="9D9672C222B728A7EDB7A2FC7700278C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. mexicanum" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mexicanum">
<emphasis id="548F1B52698230DD7A83537150F47881" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. mexicanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="142834A422FFD412242B8EE20752237F" originalValue="Cobos-Villagrán">Cobos-Villagran</normalizedToken>
, Raymundo, Calvillo-Medina &amp; R. Valenz and 
<taxonomicName id="7BB5BCFAA449BCE78AFD084F5B85D764" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. hongheense" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hongheense">
<emphasis id="ADEA80B0CBCE3F47AB6FDED305FDE11F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. hongheense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wanas. It should be noted that 
<taxonomicName id="83391CF329A9DE47543B9A5A2486D892" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. fuscum" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscum">
<emphasis id="AE9BEC0E6A175EF86D781917064C0EBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. fuscum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ellis &amp; Everh.) J.L. Bezerra &amp; Kimbr. and 
<taxonomicName id="4D9959947BDBDE5F3613961075507545" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. minor" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="7FEB76B677590C7D0F171A0CA25A437E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Cooke) A. Pande are not considered because the first belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="5D21FFC3DBC9A1CCEE574F051D641D64" authorityName="P.A.Saccardo" authorityYear="1883" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Patellariaceae" genus="Tryblidiella" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Tryblidiella" order="Patellariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5CE8CE0CAEE41D578A3B70BA94507066" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tryblidiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the second is a 
<emphasis id="035240B975C115EE65AA01E8CEC401E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">nom. inval.</emphasis>
, because the basionym was not indicated and bibliographic reference omitted (Art. 41.5, see Art. 41.7, Melbourne).
</paragraph>
